## Joins and Includes Performance

### When to Use Each

```ruby
# includes: Load associations to avoid N+1
articles = Article.includes(:user)
articles.each { |a| puts a.user.name }  # No N+1

# joins: Filter by association (doesn't load association)
Article.joins(:user).where(users: { active: true })

# eager_load: Load associations with LEFT JOIN
Article.eager_load(:user).where(users: { active: true })

# preload: Load associations with separate query
Article.preload(:user)

# Combine: Filter with joins, load with includes
Article.joins(:category)
       .includes(:user, :tags)
       .where(categories: { name: 'Tech' })
```

